[{"id":"VH985640","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p><img alt=\"Measures 6 through 12 of a piece for piano. The key signature has two flats. Starting in measure 8, the time signature is six-four. The music in question consists of two melodic gestures harmonized by several repeated chords. The first melodic gesture spans from the second half of measure 8 to the first half of measure 10. The second melodic gesture spans from the second half of measure 10 to the first half of measure 12. The melody and accompaniment in the first half of each gesture are nearly identical. The melody opens with an eighth rest on beat four followed by eighth notes C4, D4, F-sharp4, B-flat4, and A4. The melody moves to a dotted half G4 on the downbeat of the following measure. This is harmonized by a repeated G minor chord in the lower voices. The melody and accompaniment in the second half of each gesture have the same rhythms but different pitches. In the first gesture, the melody consists of dotted half notes D5 and C5, accompanied by repeated quarter note first-inversion G minor and half diminished A 7 chords. In the second gesture, the melody consists of dotted half notes E-natural4 and F-sharp4, accompanied by repeated quarter note A dominant seventh and D major chords.\" class=\"text-left\" height=\"309\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH985640.g02.png\" width=\"650\" /></p>\n\n<p>The relationship between the passage in the second half of measure&nbsp;8 through the first half of measure&nbsp;10 and the passage in the second half of measure&nbsp;10 to the first half of measure&nbsp;12 is best described as</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH985640_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">transposed repetition</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">varied repetition</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">augmentation</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">diminution</p>"],"answer":1}]